<p>AI and machine learning pose the same threat to white collar professionals in the 21st century that motive power did to blue collar workers in the 20th.</p>
<p>Job losses from automation don’t need to be massive to produce massive social dislocation. Remember that in the worst of the Great Depression, the unemployment rate was “only” 25%, and that nearly lead to violent revolution.</p>
<p>As machines produce more and more of the wealth, the old Lockean notion of ownership will be challenged. If a machine can extract natural resources, convert them into finished goods, then who is the rightful owner of the wealth produced?</p>
